From: Tomoatsu Shimada <shimada@walbrix.com>
Subject: [PATCH] rdp-view-creator-avc: Fall back without HOST_CACHED if no
 matching memory type

The VAAPI AVC view creator allocates its state buffer requesting
HOST_VISIBLE | HOST_COHERENT | HOST_CACHED simultaneously.  On some
integrated GPUs (observed on Intel UHD Graphics 600 / Gemini Lake with
Mesa ANV) no single Vulkan memory type satisfies all three at once:
HOST_COHERENT (write-combined) and HOST_CACHED are exposed on separate
memory types only.  As a result, get_memory_type_index() fails with
"Failed to find memory type index", the VAAPI encode session is never
created, and grd silently falls back to the software RFX progressive
path -- pegging the CPU when screen content changes.

HOST_CACHED is only a CPU-readback performance hint, not a correctness
requirement, so retry the allocation without it when the first attempt
fails.  Drivers that do expose a memory type with all three bits (e.g.
recent Intel Xe, AMD) continue to use it as before.

---
 src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c | 14 +++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c b/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c
--- a/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c
+++ b/src/grd-rdp-view-creator-avc.c
@@ -671,9 +671,21 @@ create_state_buffer (GrdRdpViewCreatorAVC  *view_creator_avc,

   *state_buffer_host = grd_vk_buffer_new (view_creator_avc->device,
                                           &buffer_descriptor,
-                                          error);
+                                          NULL);
   if (!(*state_buffer_host))
-    return FALSE;
+    {
+      /* HOST_CACHED and HOST_COHERENT do not coexist in any memory type on
+       * some integrated GPUs (e.g. Intel Gemini Lake with Mesa ANV). The
+       * HOST_CACHED bit is only a CPU-readback performance hint, so retry
+       * without it if the first allocation fails. */
+      buffer_descriptor.memory_flags = VK_MEMORY_PROPERTY_HOST_VISIBLE_BIT |
+                                       VK_MEMORY_PROPERTY_HOST_COHERENT_BIT;
+      *state_buffer_host = grd_vk_buffer_new (view_creator_avc->device,
+                                              &buffer_descriptor,
+                                              error);
+      if (!(*state_buffer_host))
+        return FALSE;
+    }

   memory = grd_vk_buffer_get_memory (*state_buffer_host);

